15,01Droplets accumulate,
15,01Take hold of the tiny hairs of my body,
15,01Absorbed with a dull thud into my clothes.
15,01My body is a fragile braille masterpiece
15,01Detailed by wind-blown goosebumps.

15,01Concrete, dense as it is,
15,01Is invaded in much the same manner.
15,01Air is pushed up from the cracks
15,01To make way for the moisture.

15,01I feel the larger drops slide down my arms
15,01And down the center of my back,
15,01Gaining weight with the pulling of
15,01Present smaller drops. Momentum.

15,01Shift and lay.
15,01Try and be concrete.
15,01Let the water fill me in.
15,01Let something fill me.
15,01Let anything. Be concrete.
